messages.message:
Have a quick couple of questions
1. So when I run cs start, I see that webpack failed to start. Is that normal? Everything else seems to start normally.
2. In Matt's tech talk, I didn't see a command for compiling all services. Is that possible?
For #2. `cs restart` basically compiles and restart everything
You can also do `cd $IB_HOME && cs build` to build everything without restarting any services, and `make -C <path to service> build-docker` to build a single service.
